# Agent Development

A separate `agent_requirements.txt` is used for the agent to avoid package conflicts and keep the agent code portable.

## Logging the Agent

To log the Agent in MLflow, write the agent pipeline using `%%writefile app.py` so that an `app.py` file is created and logged with the Agent artifacts.

## Tool calling

The agent uses [Unity Catalog functions](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/generative-ai/agent-framework/create-custom-tool) for tools. The notebook creates UC functions (e.g. `ask_ai`, `summarize`, `translate`) from inline SQL templates and registers them in the catalog/schema. Vector search is configured via the agent's model config (`vector_search_config`), not as a separate UC function.

Tools are loaded via [UCFunctionToolkit](https://python.langchain.com/api_reference/community/tools/langchain_community.tools.databricks.tool.UCFunctionToolkit.html). You can comment out any function names in the tool list that you do not want the agent to use.